OL,3,CPublic inquiry into Omagh bomb to
OL,4,Cbegin hearings
OL,6,FThe Irish Government has formally
OL,7,Fagreed to provide assistance to the
OL,8,Finquiry.
OL,10,FIn his opening statement to the
OL,11,Finquiry last year, Lord Turnbull said
OL,12,Fthe pain of bereavement and trauma
OL,13,Fcaused by the dissident republican
OL,14,Fbomb attack spread beyond Omagh,
OL,15,FNorthern Ireland and Ireland to
OL,16,Ffamilies from England and Spain.
OL,18,FHe said the inquiry will undertake its
OL,19,Ftask "rigorously and fearlessly", and
OL,20,Femphasised the "defining character of
OL,21,Fthe inquiry must be its independence".
